metadata.name: Hatchet: Uzumaki #48
metadata.description:
Hatchet: Uzumaki (渦巻) is the first piece in Hatchet; a generative art series that hatches an arrangement of segmented polygons generated via a Voronoi diagram. Uzumaki (Japanese for 'spiral') arranges it's polygons in a multi-armed spiral with varying arm lengths and twist intensities.

All pieces in Hatchet are composed to emulate the aesthetic of colored pencils on paper. Each piece is capable of exporting its hatch lines as a well-labeled SVG document. This will allow collectors interested in plotting to create physical renditions of their iteration.

The following key-press actions are supported on the token:
- 'r': Animate the erasure and re-drawing of the hatch lines.
- 's': Export the SVG document describing the arrangement of hatch lines.

metadata.name: Balanced #38
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced

metadata.name: 🌱 Potted & Printed #343
metadata.description:
Note:
This token is CPU intensive and may take long to render. 

---

Description:
Potted & Printed is a series of generative potted plants. There are 7 species and they have been selected from my very many indoor plants at home. The species are: 
- Snake Plant
- Monstera Adonsonii
- Alocasia
- Bird's Nest Fern
- False Shamrock
- Ponytail Palm
- Parlor Palm

---

Saving:
To save a 3500x3500 PNG file, double click/tap or press 's' 

---

Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao) with p5.js

metadata.description:
A unique sketch of an imaginary weave. Color palette inspired by the great works of Anni Albers, Gunta Stölzl, Sophie Taeuber-Arp, or Hilma af Klint.

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #186
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).
